# Alogyan — Firestore Schema Design

> **Database**: Firebase Firestore (NoSQL Document Store)  
> **Multi-tenancy**: `teacherId` field on every document (row-level isolation)  
> **Naming**: Collections = `camelCase`, Fields = `camelCase`

---

## Design Principles

| Principle | Application |
|-----------|-------------|
| **No JOINs** | Denormalize read-frequent names (studentName, batchName) into child docs |
| **Query-first** | Schema shaped by UI queries, not normalization theory |
| **teacherId on everything** | Single field enables multi-tenant security rules |
| **Counters as fields** | `currentSeats`, `totalStudents` stored on parent, not counted at query time |
| **Composite key IDs** | `attendance` uses `{batchId}_{YYYY-MM-DD}` to enable direct lookup |
| **Soft deletes** | `isArchived: true` instead of deletion — preserve fee and attendance history |

---

## Multi-Tenant Structure

```
Every collection document MUST have:
  teacherId: string   ← The owning teacher's Firebase UID

All queries MUST always filter by teacherId FIRST:
  db.collection('students').where('teacherId', '==', uid).where(...)
  
API layer enforces this: teacherId extracted from verified Firebase token,
never from request body.
```

---

## Collection: `teachers`

The root entity. One document per registered teacher.

```typescript
interface Teacher {
  // Identity
  id: string;                    // Firebase UID (document ID)
  name: string;                  // "Rajesh Sharma"
  email: string;
  phone: string;                 // "+919876543210"
  photoUrl?: string;             // Firebase Storage URL

  // Public Profile
  slug: string;                  // "rajesh-sharma-delhi" (unique, URL-safe)
  bio?: string;                  // 500 chars max
  subjects: string[];            // ["Mathematics", "Physics"]
  location: string;              // "Delhi, India"
  experience?: number;           // Years (optional)
  qualifications?: string[];     // ["B.Sc Math", "B.Ed"]
  languages?: string[];          // ["Hindi", "English"]
  
  // Discovery
  isPublic: boolean;             // Show on public search
  isVerified: boolean;           // Admin-verified badge
  rating?: number;               // 1.0–5.0 (future)
  reviewCount?: number;          // Denormalized count

  // Plan & Billing
  plan: 'free' | 'pro' | 'enterprise';
  planExpiresAt?: Timestamp;

  // Stats (denormalized counters — updated on write)
  totalStudents: number;         // Active enrolled students
  totalBatches: number;          // Active batches

  // System
  createdAt: Timestamp;
  updatedAt: Timestamp;
  lastActiveAt?: Timestamp;
}
```

**Document ID**: Firebase Auth UID  
**Indexes needed**: `slug` (single field, for public profile lookup)

---

## Collection: `students`

One document per student. Scoped to a teacher.

```typescript
interface Student {
  id: string;                    // Auto-generated Firestore ID
  teacherId: string;             // Owner (for multi-tenancy)

  // Identity
  name: string;
  phone: string;                 // Student's phone (WhatsApp capable)
  parentPhone?: string;          // Guardian's phone
  email?: string;

  // Academics
  grade?: string;                // "Class 10", "JEE Dropper", "Grade 5"
  school?: string;

  // Location
  address?: string;
  city?: string;

  // Status
  isArchived: boolean;           // Soft delete — default: false
  archivedAt?: Timestamp;

  // Metadata (denormalized for fast filters)
  activeBatchIds: string[];      // Currently enrolled batch IDs
  
  // System
  createdAt: Timestamp;
  updatedAt: Timestamp;
}
```

**Indexes**:
```yaml
students:
  - [teacherId ASC, isArchived ASC, createdAt DESC]   # List all active students
  - [teacherId ASC, isArchived ASC, name ASC]          # Alphabetical list
  - [teacherId ASC, activeBatchIds ARRAY_CONTAINS]     # Students in a batch (via array)
```

> **Why `activeBatchIds` array?** Avoids expensive cross-collection query. Updated on enrollment/unenrollment.

---

## Collection: `batches`

A batch = one course/class a teacher runs (e.g., "JEE Maths Batch 2024").

```typescript
interface Batch {
  id: string;
  teacherId: string;

  // Info
  name: string;                  // "JEE Physics Morning Batch"
  subject: string;               // "Physics"
  description?: string;

  // Schedule
  schedule: {
    days: Array<'Mon'|'Tue'|'Wed'|'Thu'|'Fri'|'Sat'|'Sun'>;
    startTime: string;           // "09:00" (24-hr, local)
    endTime: string;             // "10:30"
    timezone: string;            // "Asia/Kolkata"
  };

  // Fees
  feesPerMonth: number;          // INR, e.g. 2500
  feesDueDay: number;            // Day of month, e.g. 5 (due by 5th)

  // Capacity
  maxSeats: number;
  currentSeats: number;          // Denormalized counter

  // Status
  status: 'active' | 'paused' | 'closed';
  term?: string;                 // "2024-Q1" or "Jan 2024"

  // System
  createdAt: Timestamp;
  updatedAt: Timestamp;
}
```

**Indexes**:
```yaml
batches:
  - [teacherId ASC, status ASC, createdAt DESC]   # Active batches list
  - [teacherId ASC, subject ASC]                   # Filter by subject
```

---

## Collection: `enrollments`

Junction table: Student ↔ Batch (many-to-many).  
Preserved even after student leaves (for fee history continuity).

```typescript
interface Enrollment {
  id: string;
  teacherId: string;

  studentId: string;
  batchId: string;

  // Denormalized for display (avoids extra reads)
  studentName: string;
  batchName: string;

  // Dates
  enrolledAt: Timestamp;
  leftAt?: Timestamp;            // Null = still active

  // Status
  isActive: boolean;

  // System
  createdAt: Timestamp;
}
```

**Indexes**:
```yaml
enrollments:
  - [teacherId ASC, batchId ASC, isActive ASC]           # Students in a batch
  - [teacherId ASC, studentId ASC, isActive ASC]         # Batches a student is in
  - [teacherId ASC, batchId ASC, enrolledAt DESC]        # Audit timeline
```

---

## Collection: `attendance`

**Document ID pattern**: `{batchId}_{YYYY-MM-DD}` — one doc per batch per day.  
This enables O(1) lookup with `db.doc('attendance/{batchId}_{date}').get()`.

```typescript
interface AttendanceRecord {
  id: string;                    // "{batchId}_{YYYY-MM-DD}"
  teacherId: string;
  batchId: string;
  date: string;                  // "2024-03-15" (YYYY-MM-DD)
  
  // Month for range queries
  month: string;                 // "2024-03" (YYYY-MM)

  // The core: one entry per enrolled student
  records: {
    [studentId: string]: 'present' | 'absent' | 'leave' | 'holiday';
  };

  // Denormalized counts for fast summary
  presentCount: number;
  absentCount: number;
  totalStudents: number;

  // Metadata
  isHoliday: boolean;            // Entire day marked holiday
  holidayReason?: string;
  markedBy: string;              // teacherId
  markedAt: Timestamp;
  updatedAt: Timestamp;
}
```

**Indexes**:
```yaml
attendance:
  - [teacherId ASC, batchId ASC, date DESC]              # Batch attendance history
  - [teacherId ASC, batchId ASC, month ASC]              # Monthly view for a batch
```

> **Why `month` field?** Firestore can't range-filter on a substring of `date`. The `month` field enables: `where('month', '==', '2024-03')`.

---

## Collection: `feeRecords`

One record per student per month per batch.  
Fee is generated in bulk by teacher for all enrolled students.

```typescript
interface FeeRecord {
  id: string;
  teacherId: string;
  studentId: string;
  batchId: string;

  // Denormalized for display
  studentName: string;
  batchName: string;

  // Fee details
  amount: number;                // Total fee for the month (INR)
  month: string;                 // "2024-03" (billing month)
  dueDate: Timestamp;            // Actual due date

  // Payment status
  status: 'pending' | 'partial' | 'paid' | 'waived' | 'overdue';
  
  // Payment tracking
  paidAmount: number;            // 0 by default, updated on payment
  balanceAmount: number;         // amount - paidAmount (denormalized)
  
  // Last payment reference
  lastPaymentId?: string;        // points to payments/{id}
  lastPaymentAt?: Timestamp;

  // Notes
  memo?: string;                 // Teacher's note

  // System
  generatedAt: Timestamp;
  updatedAt: Timestamp;
}
```

**Indexes**:
```yaml
feeRecords:
  - [teacherId ASC, status ASC, dueDate ASC]             # Overdue / pending view
  - [teacherId ASC, studentId ASC, month DESC]           # Student fee history
  - [teacherId ASC, batchId ASC, month ASC]              # Batch fee report
  - [teacherId ASC, month ASC, status ASC]               # Monthly collection report
```

---

## Collection: `payments`

Each payment event (a student pays, partially or fully).  
Separate from feeRecords — one feeRecord can have multiple payments.

```typescript
interface Payment {
  id: string;
  teacherId: string;
  feeRecordId: string;           // Link to parent fee record
  studentId: string;
  batchId: string;

  // Denormalized
  studentName: string;
  month: string;                 // "2024-03"

  // Payment info
  amount: number;                // Amount paid in this transaction
  mode: 'cash' | 'upi' | 'cheque' | 'bank_transfer' | 'other';
  
  // Mode-specific details
  upiTransactionId?: string;
  chequeNumber?: string;
  chequeDate?: string;
  bankRef?: string;
  notes?: string;

  // Who recorded
  recordedBy: string;            // teacherId
  paidAt: Timestamp;             // When payment was made (can be past date)
  createdAt: Timestamp;          // When it was entered in system
}
```

**Indexes**:
```yaml
payments:
  - [teacherId ASC, feeRecordId ASC, paidAt DESC]        # Payments for a fee record
  - [teacherId ASC, studentId ASC, paidAt DESC]          # Student payment history
  - [teacherId ASC, month ASC, paidAt DESC]              # Monthly collection log
  - [teacherId ASC, mode ASC, paidAt DESC]               # By payment mode
```

---

## Collection: `notes`

Study material / handouts uploaded by teacher. Metadata only — files in Firebase Storage.

```typescript
interface Note {
  id: string;
  teacherId: string;
  batchId?: string;              // null = visible to all students of teacher

  // Content
  title: string;
  description?: string;
  subject?: string;
  tags?: string[];               // ["algebra", "chapter-3"]

  // File
  storageUrl: string;            // Firebase Storage download URL
  storagePath: string;           // Storage path (for deletion)
  fileType: 'pdf' | 'image' | 'doc' | 'ppt' | 'video' | 'other';
  fileSizeBytes: number;
  fileName: string;              // Original filename

  // Visibility
  isPublic: boolean;             // Future: share publicly

  // System
  uploadedAt: Timestamp;
  createdAt: Timestamp;
}
```

**Indexes**:
```yaml
notes:
  - [teacherId ASC, batchId ASC, uploadedAt DESC]        # Notes for a batch
  - [teacherId ASC, subject ASC, uploadedAt DESC]        # Filter by subject
  - [teacherId ASC, tags ARRAY_CONTAINS, uploadedAt DESC] # Tag filter
```

---

## Collection: `announcements`

Messages published to students (in-app + WhatsApp link).

```typescript
interface Announcement {
  id: string;
  teacherId: string;
  targetBatchId?: string;        // null = all students of teacher

  // Content
  title: string;
  message: string;               // Max 1000 chars
  attachmentUrl?: string;        // Optional file/image

  // Channels
  channels: Array<'inapp' | 'whatsapp'>;

  // State
  isPinned: boolean;
  status: 'draft' | 'scheduled' | 'sent' | 'cancelled';

  // Timing
  scheduledAt?: Timestamp;       // For future announcements
  sentAt?: Timestamp;

  // Stats
  recipientCount: number;        // Denormalized at send time

  // System
  createdAt: Timestamp;
  updatedAt: Timestamp;
}
```

**Indexes**:
```yaml
announcements:
  - [teacherId ASC, isPinned DESC, sentAt DESC]          # Pinned first, then recent
  - [teacherId ASC, targetBatchId ASC, sentAt DESC]      # Per-batch announcements
  - [teacherId ASC, status ASC, scheduledAt ASC]         # Scheduled announcements queue
```

---

## Collection: `tests`

A test or quiz (online or offline) published by teacher.

```typescript
interface Test {
  id: string;
  teacherId: string;
  batchId: string;

  // Info
  title: string;
  subject: string;
  description?: string;
  date: string;                  // "2024-03-20" (YYYY-MM-DD, test date)
  totalMarks: number;
  passingMarks?: number;
  durationMinutes?: number;

  // Type
  type: 'online' | 'offline';

  // Online test: questions embedded
  questions?: Array<{
    id: string;
    text: string;
    options?: string[];          // MCQ options
    correct?: string | number;   // Index or value
    marks: number;
    type: 'mcq' | 'short' | 'long';
  }>;

  // Offline test: PDF upload
  pdfUrl?: string;
  pdfStoragePath?: string;

  // Status
  status: 'draft' | 'published' | 'closed';
  publishedAt?: Timestamp;

  // Stats (denormalized after grading)
  attemptCount?: number;
  averageScore?: number;
  highestScore?: number;

  // System
  createdAt: Timestamp;
  updatedAt: Timestamp;
}
```

**Sub-collection alternative**: For large question sets, use `tests/{testId}/questions/{questionId}`.  
Rule of thumb: Embed if < 50 questions; sub-collection if ≥ 50.

---

## Collection: `testResults`

One record per student per test.

```typescript
interface TestResult {
  id: string;                    // "{testId}_{studentId}" for direct lookup
  teacherId: string;
  testId: string;
  studentId: string;
  batchId: string;

  // Denormalized
  studentName: string;
  testTitle: string;

  // Score
  score: number;
  totalMarks: number;
  percentage: number;            // Denormalized: (score/totalMarks)*100
  isPassed?: boolean;

  // Online test only
  answers?: {
    [questionId: string]: string | number;
  };
  timeTaken?: number;            // Seconds

  // Offline test only — marks entered by teacher
  marksBreakdown?: {
    [section: string]: number;
  };

  // Metadata
  submittedAt: Timestamp;        // When student submitted / teacher entered
  gradedBy?: string;             // teacherId (for offline)
  createdAt: Timestamp;
}
```

**Indexes**:
```yaml
testResults:
  - [teacherId ASC, testId ASC, score DESC]              # Leaderboard
  - [teacherId ASC, studentId ASC, submittedAt DESC]     # Per-student results
  - [teacherId ASC, batchId ASC, submittedAt DESC]       # Batch results
```

---

## Collection: `leads`

Prospective students who submitted enquiry from teacher's public profile.

```typescript
interface Lead {
  id: string;
  teacherId: string;

  // From form
  name: string;
  phone: string;
  email?: string;
  grade?: string;
  message?: string;

  // Source tracking
  source: 'public_profile' | 'referral' | 'direct';
  sourceSlug?: string;           // Teacher slug they landed on

  // CRM Status
  status: 'new' | 'contacted' | 'interested' | 'enrolled' | 'rejected' | 'dropped';
  
  // Follow-up
  followUpNotes?: string;
  followUpAt?: Timestamp;
  lastContactedAt?: Timestamp;

  // Conversion
  convertedStudentId?: string;   // If enrolled, links to student doc

  // Rate limiting protection
  submittedFromIp?: string;      // Hashed IP (not plain text)

  // System
  receivedAt: Timestamp;
  updatedAt: Timestamp;
}
```

**Indexes**:
```yaml
leads:
  - [teacherId ASC, status ASC, receivedAt DESC]         # CRM pipeline view
  - [teacherId ASC, receivedAt DESC]                     # All leads timeline
```

---

## Relationships Map

```
teachers (1)
  │
  ├──< students (N)          teacherId FK
  │       │
  ├──< batches (N)           teacherId FK  
  │       │
  │       ├──── enrollments  ──── students (many-to-many via enrollments collection)
  │       │
  │       ├──< attendance    batchId + date (compound ID)
  │       │
  │       ├──< feeRecords    batchId + studentId + month
  │       │        │
  │       │        └──< payments    feeRecordId
  │       │
  │       ├──< tests         batchId
  │       │        │
  │       │        └──< testResults   testId + studentId (compound ID)
  │       │
  │       ├──< notes         batchId (nullable)
  │       └──< announcements targetBatchId (nullable)
  │
  └──< leads (N)             teacherId FK
```

---

