## Firestore Security Rules

```javascript
rules_version = '2';
service cloud.firestore {
  match /databases/{database}/documents {

    // Helper: verify the calling user is the document's owner
    function isOwner(teacherId) {
      return request.auth != null && request.auth.uid == teacherId;
    }

    // Helper: the request is coming from a valid authenticated teacher
    function isAuthenticated() {
      return request.auth != null;
    }

    // ── Teachers ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
    match /teachers/{teacherId} {
      // Teacher can read/write their own doc
      allow read, write: if isOwner(teacherId);
      // Public profiles visible to anyone
      allow read: if resource.data.isPublic == true;
    }

    // ── Students ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
    match /students/{studentId} {
      allow read, write: if isAuthenticated() 
        && request.auth.uid == resource.data.teacherId;
      allow create: if isAuthenticated()
        && request.auth.uid == request.resource.data.teacherId;
    }

    // ── Batches ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
    match /batches/{batchId} {
      allow read, write: if isAuthenticated()
        && request.auth.uid == resource.data.teacherId;
      allow create: if isAuthenticated()
        && request.auth.uid == request.resource.data.teacherId;
    }

    // ── Enrollments ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────
    match /enrollments/{enrollmentId} {
      allow read, write: if isAuthenticated()
        && request.auth.uid == resource.data.teacherId;
      allow create: if isAuthenticated()
        && request.auth.uid == request.resource.data.teacherId;
    }

    // ── Attendance ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
    match /attendance/{attendanceId} {
      allow read, write: if isAuthenticated()
        && request.auth.uid == resource.data.teacherId;
      allow create: if isAuthenticated()
        && request.auth.uid == request.resource.data.teacherId;
    }

    // ── Fee Records ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────
    match /feeRecords/{feeRecordId} {
      allow read, write: if isAuthenticated()
        && request.auth.uid == resource.data.teacherId;
      allow create: if isAuthenticated()
        && request.auth.uid == request.resource.data.teacherId;
    }

    // ── Payments ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
    match /payments/{paymentId} {
      allow read, write: if isAuthenticated()
        && request.auth.uid == resource.data.teacherId;
      allow create: if isAuthenticated()
        && request.auth.uid == request.resource.data.teacherId;
    }

    // ── Notes ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
    match /notes/{noteId} {
      allow read, write: if isAuthenticated()
        && request.auth.uid == resource.data.teacherId;
      allow create: if isAuthenticated()
        && request.auth.uid == request.resource.data.teacherId;
    }

    // ── Tests ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
    match /tests/{testId} {
      allow read, write: if isAuthenticated()
        && request.auth.uid == resource.data.teacherId;
      allow create: if isAuthenticated()
        && request.auth.uid == request.resource.data.teacherId;
    }

    // ── Test Results ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
    match /testResults/{resultId} {
      allow read, write: if isAuthenticated()
        && request.auth.uid == resource.data.teacherId;
      allow create: if isAuthenticated()
        && request.auth.uid == request.resource.data.teacherId;
    }

    // ── Announcements ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
    match /announcements/{announcementId} {
      allow read, write: if isAuthenticated()
        && request.auth.uid == resource.data.teacherId;
      allow create: if isAuthenticated()
        && request.auth.uid == request.resource.data.teacherId;
    }

    // ── Leads ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
    match /leads/{leadId} {
      // Anyone can create a lead (public form — rate-limited at API layer)
      allow create: if true;
      // Only the teacher who owns it can read/update
      allow read, write: if isAuthenticated()
        && request.auth.uid == resource.data.teacherId;
    }
  }
}
```

> ⚠️ These Firestore rules are a **second layer of defense**. The Node.js backend always enforces `teacherId` ownership checks as the **first layer**. Never rely on Firestore rules alone.

---

## Denormalization Decisions

| Denormalized Field | Location | Why |
|-------------------|----------|-----|
| `studentName` | enrollments, feeRecords, payments, testResults | Show student name without extra read |
| `batchName` | enrollments, feeRecords | Show batch name in student history |
| `currentSeats` | batches | Avoid counting enrollments on every render |
| `totalStudents`, `totalBatches` | teachers | Dashboard KPIs without aggregation |
| `activeBatchIds` | students | Filter students in a batch via array-contains |
| `balanceAmount` | feeRecords | `amount - paidAmount` (avoid calculation in UI) |
| `percentage` | testResults | `(score/totalMarks)*100` (avoid in UI) |
| `presentCount`, `absentCount` | attendance | Monthly summary without scanning records map |
| `attemptCount`, `averageScore` | tests | Batch result summary without scanning testResults |

> **Update strategy**: Use Firestore Transactions or batch writes when updating a document AND its denormalized copies. Service layer handles this.

---

## Document Size Estimates

| Collection | Avg Doc Size | 100K teachers × 100 students |
|-----------|-------------|------------------------------|
| teachers | ~2 KB | 200 MB |
| students | ~1 KB | 10 GB |
| batches | ~1 KB | varies |
| enrollments | ~500 B | varies |
| attendance | ~5 KB (100 students) | significant |
| feeRecords | ~800 B | varies |
| payments | ~600 B | varies |

> Firestore performance degrades for documents > **1 MB**. Attendance docs grow with student count — for batches > 200 students, consider splitting: `attendance/{batchId}_{date}_A`, `attendance/{batchId}_{date}_B`.

---

